Ngữ cảnh: JARDINE MATHESON INFORMATION SECURITY POLICY GUIDELINES CONFIDENTIAL > A2. System Hardening > A2.4. Policy Statements > Configuration Management
Nội dung chính: [Configuration Management]
1. Configuration review must be performed on all system and network components according to the
relevant configuration standards prior to production implementation and at least annually
thereafter. Below are the basic principles of the review practice: [Baseline]
• Installing minimum hardware, software, and services necessary to meet business
requirements;
• Installing necessary patches;
• Installing the most secure and up-to-date versions of applications;
• Limiting privileges and user access based on the least privilege principle;
• Configuring security settings as appropriate, allowing approved user activities only;
• Enabling logging;
• Changing all default passwords and secrets; and
• Performing testing to ensure that the configuration performs as expected.

